net.proteusframework.core.metric

Class UnknownMetric

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.proteusframework.core.metric.Metric
      • net.proteusframework.core.metric.UnknownMetric
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Cloneable

    public final class UnknownMetric
extends Metric
    The UnknownMetric class is used to represent a metric whose units are unknown. This class should rarely be used and is normally equivalent to using the PixelMetric class when applying conversions to different unit systems. It is provided for cases when the units are not known and instead of using PixelMetric and assuming that the pixel unit is correct, this class is used to indicate the actual units are unknown.
    Author:
    Pat Double (double@i2rd.com)
